cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DC

This paper is about improving the efficiency of inference algorithms in probabilistic programming languages (PPLs) through automatic specialization. This topic is closely related to programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE) since PPLs are used to build machine learning models and software systems. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of caching and generating C code, which are topics in distributed computing (cs.DC).
